            "answer_text": "NaCl has an FCC structure because the Na ions form an FCC lattice and the Cl ions also form an FCC lattice. Each Na ion has 6 Cl nearest neighbors, and each Cl ion has 6 Na nearest neighbors. Each Na ion has 12 Na second-nearest neighbors, and each Cl ion has 12 Cl second-nearest neighbors. If that isn\u2019t clear for you, then you need to find a ball-and-stick model to look at. ",
